{
  "texts": [
    "The software QCAmap 2020 was used for the coding process, aligning the extracted data with predefined categories (Mayring, 2021).",
    "Each piece of extracted data was reviewed and allocated to the most relevant category based on its content.",
    "To further deepen the analysis, inductive category formation was employed to create subcategories within the initially defined primary categories.",
    "The use of inductive category formation allows for a flexible and openended approach to data analysis, while still providing a systematic and rigorous method for identifying and categorizing relevant Modified step model for inductive category formation (adapted from (Mayring, 2000)).",
    "Frontiers in Blockchain frontiersin.org information."
  ]
}